# WordPress Security and Data Handling

- Validate and sanitize all input from request data, options, and metadata.
- Escape all output by context: `esc_html`, `esc_attr`, `esc_url`, `wp_kses_post`.
- Protect all state-changing actions with nonces and verify capabilities.
- Never trust `$_GET`, `$_POST`, `$_REQUEST`, `$_COOKIE`; sanitize before use.
- Use `$wpdb->prepare()` for custom SQL and avoid unsafe string concatenation.
- Disallow `eval`, unsafe dynamic includes, and obfuscated code patterns.
- Do not expose stack traces, SQL errors, or internal paths to users.
- If rendering HTML from user content, allow only explicit safe tags and attributes.
